TITLE: Reading PDF Content in C# using PdfPig
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to open a PDF file, iterate through its pages, and extract letters, words, and images. It uses the core PdfDocument and Page classes to access document content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uglytoad/pdfpig/blob/master/docs/index.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: csharp
CODE:
```
using System.Collections.Generic;
using System.Linq;
using UglyToad.PdfPig;
using UglyToad.PdfPig.Content;

public static class Program
{
    public static void Main()
    {
        using (PdfDocument document = PdfDocument.Open(@"C:\path\to\pdffile\file.pdf"))
        {
            foreach (Page page in document.GetPages())
            {
                IReadOnlyList<Letter> letters = page.Letters;
                string example = string.Join(string.Empty, letters.Select(x => x.Value));

                IEnumerable<Word> words = page.GetWords();

                IEnumerable<IPdfImage> images = page.GetImages();
            }
        }
    }
}
```

