TITLE: Reading Words from PDF Pages in C#
DESCRIPTION: Opens a PDF document and extracts words from every page. The example demonstrates how to access page text and iterate through individual words in the document.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uglytoad/pdfpig/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
using (PdfDocument document = PdfDocument.Open(@"C:\Documents\document.pdf"))
{
	foreach (Page page in document.GetPages())
	{
		string pageText = page.Text;

		foreach (Word word in page.GetWords())
		{
			Console.WriteLine(word.Text);
		}
	}
}
```

