TITLE: Basic PDF Document Operations in C#
DESCRIPTION: Shows basic operations with PdfDocument class including opening a file, accessing page count and dimensions, and extracting text. The example also demonstrates how to handle encrypted documents with passwords.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uglytoad/pdfpig/blob/master/README.md#2025-04-18_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C#
CODE:
```
using UglyToad.PdfPig;
using UglyToad.PdfPig.Content;

using (PdfDocument document = PdfDocument.Open(@"C:\my-file.pdf"))
{
	int pageCount = document.NumberOfPages;

	// Page number starts from 1, not 0.
	Page page = document.GetPage(1);

	decimal widthInPoints = page.Width;
	decimal heightInPoints = page.Height;

	string text = page.Text;
}
```

