TITLE: Displaying Font Types and Structures in PDF
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates the hierarchy of font types in PDF, including composite fonts (Type0 with CIDFonts) and simple fonts (Type 1, MMType1, Type 3, and TrueType). It provides a clear visual representation of the font type relationships.
SOURCE: https://github.com/uglytoad/pdfpig/blob/master/font-notes.md#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: plaintext
CODE:
```
------	Composite Fonts -------

	Type0 (Composed of glyphs from a CIDFont)

		Children:

		CIDFont 	CIDFontType0	(Type 1 font glyph descriptions)
				CIDFontType2	(TrueType font glyph descriptions)

------	Simple Fonts Below -------

	Type 1	Type 1 (defines gylphs using type 1 font technology)
		MMType1 (multiple master font - extends type 1 fonts to support many typefaces for a single font)

	Type 3	(defines glyphs with streams of PDF graphics operations)

	TrueType (from the TrueType font format)
```

